==English==
===Noun===
===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} ''Χιμαιρα'', a she goat, through Latin chimera. The [[fabulous]] monster in Lycea. Killed by Bellerophon.

'''chimera'''

#A monster represented as vomiting flames, and as having the head of a lion, the body of a goat, and the tail of a dragon.
#A vain, foolish, or incongruous fancy, or creature of the imagination; as, the chimera of an author.

